LiveStride Android Build / Pixel Install Cheat Sheet
=====================================================

PROJECT ROOT
------------
Use this folder for terminal commands:

C:\Users\kylei\Desktop\Live Stride\livestride-app

Important:
- This is the Desktop version of the project.
- Do NOT accidentally use:
  C:\Users\kylei\livestride-app


1) OPEN COMMAND PROMPT AT PROJECT ROOT
--------------------------------------
Run:

cd /d "C:\Users\kylei\Desktop\Live Stride\livestride-app"


2) SYNC WEB FILES INTO ANDROID
------------------------------
Run this after changing index.html, main.js, or other web files:

npx cap sync android


3) PATCH PROGUARD FILE REFERENCES IF BUILD FAILS
------------------------------------------------
If Android Studio gives an error about:

getDefaultProguardFile('proguard-android.txt')

Run this from the project root:

powershell -NoProfile -Command "Get-ChildItem -Recurse -Filter build.gradle | ForEach-Object { (Get-Content $_.FullName) -replace 'proguard-android\.txt', 'proguard-android-optimize.txt' | Set-Content $_.FullName }"

Then go back to Android Studio and run:

File > Sync Project with Gradle Files


4) BUILD A NEW APK IN ANDROID STUDIO
------------------------------------
Open this Android project:

C:\Users\kylei\Desktop\Live Stride\livestride-app\android

Then in Android Studio:

Build > Clean Project
Build > Build Bundle(s) / APK(s) > Build APK(s)

The APK should appear here:

C:\Users\kylei\Desktop\Live Stride\livestride-app\android\app\build\outputs\apk\debug\app-debug.apk

Check the Date Modified to make sure it updated.


5) CHECK THAT THE PIXEL IS CONNECTED
------------------------------------
Run:

"%LOCALAPPDATA%\Android\Sdk\platform-tools\adb.exe" devices

On the Pixel, accept the "Allow USB debugging?" prompt if it appears.

You should see a device listed.


6) INSTALL THE APK ON THE PIXEL
-------------------------------
Run:

"%LOCALAPPDATA%\Android\Sdk\platform-tools\adb.exe" install -r "C:\Users\kylei\Desktop\Live Stride\livestride-app\android\app\build\outputs\apk\debug\app-debug.apk"

The -r means reinstall/update the app while keeping it installed.


7) QUICK FULL WORKFLOW
----------------------
Use this sequence after changing app code:

cd /d "C:\Users\kylei\Desktop\Live Stride\livestride-app"

npx cap sync android

Then in Android Studio:
Build > Clean Project
Build > Build Bundle(s) / APK(s) > Build APK(s)

Then install to Pixel:

"%LOCALAPPDATA%\Android\Sdk\platform-tools\adb.exe" devices

"%LOCALAPPDATA%\Android\Sdk\platform-tools\adb.exe" install -r "C:\Users\kylei\Desktop\Live Stride\livestride-app\android\app\build\outputs\apk\debug\app-debug.apk"


8) PIXEL DEVELOPER MODE REMINDER
--------------------------------
On Pixel 7:

Settings > About phone > Build number
Tap Build number 7 times.

Then:

Settings > System > Developer options > USB debugging = ON

When plugging into the computer, accept:
Allow USB debugging
